findings.pleural effusions: Trace pleural effusions are noted bilaterally.
findings.liver: The liver enhances homogeneously without suspicious enhancing masses.
findings.biliary: No intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary duct dilation. The gallbladder demonstrates a fluid fluid level suggestive of biliary sludge. There is no cholelithiasis or evidence of ____.
findings.pancreas: Peripancreatic stranding, predominantly around the body of the pancreas, is consistent with known pancreatitis. There is no pancreatic duct dilatation. No peripancreatic fluid collections are seen. A 7 mm T2 hyperintensity in the neck of the pancreas likely represents a side branch IPMN. A smaller 5 mm T2 hyperintensity in the pancreatic tail is also noted.
findings.spleen: The spleen is normal in size and signal intensity.
findings.adrenal glands: The adrenal glands are normal in size and signal intensity.
findings.kidneys: A 10 mm lesion in the midpole in the left kidney demonstrates central enhancement. The lesion is T1 isointense without evidence of bulk or intravoxel fat. Bilateral renal cysts are noted.
findings.gastrointestinal tract: The stomach and intra-abdominal loops of small and large bowel are unremarkable without evidence of wall thickening or obstruction.
findings.vasculature: The portal and hepatic veins are patent. There is no abdominal aortic aneurysm.
findings.osseoous structures: The bones demonstrate normal signal intensity. The abdominal wall is unremarkable.
